        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:04PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a gusty thunderstorm over
Elmhurst, Westchester, and La Grange. The storm is nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Localized wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lyons, Westchester, Clarendon Hills, Addison, La Grange, Bellwood,
Berkeley, Hillside, River Forest, Oakbrook Terrace, Northlake,
Maywood, York Center, Westmont, Western Springs, Franklin Park, Stone
Park, Elmhurst, McCook, Hinsdale, North Riverside, Hodgkins, Melrose
Park, Oak Brook, and Lombard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
